{"id":14881035,"mediaExerciseId":"872a2c5d-c379-4099-8cdf-6c39c0b419b4","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612312,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":232,"solutions":[{"id":5965758,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **we should answer if the statement according to the U.S. Treasury security is true or false.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/31/4fb417259a46980728796caad023b2c3/6bbdf7d5295c0e24b6d1234ba4494205/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/31/4fb417259a46980728796caad023b2c3/6bbdf7d5295c0e24b6d1234ba4494205/lateximg.png","width":496}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**The statement is true, let's explain why**. The company that invests in the  U.S. Treasury security will never face a risk of a missed payment or no payment at all. The government will go bankrupt and not pay the debt.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/4fb417259a46980728796caad023b2c3/5a99b3ece3309593de867a948a686094/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/4fb417259a46980728796caad023b2c3/5a99b3ece3309593de867a948a686094/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"63106b74-366d-4260-b901-ba0ee9f22679","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":2},{"id":6373816,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"We need to determine if U.S. treasury is risk-free.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"In complete bluntness, almost nothing is risk-free in finances.\n\nNominally, from cash amount perspective, the treasury IS risk-free, as it cannot default (ie. it cannot be in the situation where it cannot pay back a financial obligation) as money WILL somehow be added in it.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"From bond perspective however, it is not totally immune against risk, as it may suffer from inflation or some external burden or the bonds aren't held to maturity, but *generally*, treasury has certain advantages that make it one of the safest option to purchase bonds from.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"In conclusion, while not **absolutely** risk-free, treasure is 'immune enough' to make bond purchasing a fairly safe venture.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"ee7054f8-f222-443e-a4a4-4ec359b5cda6","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881036,"exerciseName":"2","page":232,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"3e24752c-bff4-4886-91ac-e41cdce94bb3","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-2-3e24752c-bff4-4886-91ac-e41cdce94bb3"},{"id":14881037,"exerciseName":"3","page":232,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"60df86ae-a6ef-48cf-a675-22c8ecea1464","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-3-60df86ae-a6ef-48cf-a675-22c8ecea1464"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881034,"exerciseName":"7","page":230,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"bff7b031-489d-44b0-a12b-26591dc46811","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-7-bff7b031-489d-44b0-a12b-26591dc46811"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-1-872a2c5d-c379-4099-8cdf-6c39c0b419b4"}